A note on providers.
Providers.
Apps are wired together using injetor service.

Injector creates two typed of objects services and specialised objects.

-> Services are objects whose api is defined by the developer writing the sevice.

-> Specialised Objects confirm to specific angular framework api. these objects are on of controllers, directives, filters an animatiions.


Note that the injector needs to know how to create the recipe that you are asking it to create.
value, factory, service constant and provider.

Value recipe.

var myApp = angular.module('myApp', []);
myApp.value('clientid', 'a123456321x');
